"History: In North America, this surname (see 1 above) developed from a secondary surname or <i>dit</i> (‘also called’) name, borne by Jean Louismet <i>dit</i> Laiguille (or Louismet-Laiguille), a soldier from Dunkerque in Nord, France, who married Marie-Catherine Marquet <i>dit</i> Périgord in Quebec City, QC, in 1757."],"variants":[{"name":"Gue","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Giraud.","Altered form of French   Guyon  .","French (<b>Gué</b>): topographic name for someone who lived by a ford, <i>gué</i>, from Old French <i>wad</i> ‘ford, crossing place’. Compare   Dugue   and   Legue  ."]}]},{"name":"Lady","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>lavedi</i>, <i>levedi</i>, <i>ladi</i> ‘lady, female head of a household, woman, wife’ (Old English <i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘Morning dew’; also ‘generosity’."]}]},{"name":"Annella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Elaborated form of   Anne .  It is favoured in the Highlands of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Annella Lerue was born in 1402, in Lindsell, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She married William Alger in 1433, in Lindsell, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. She died in 1439, in her hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1402–1439":"1402–1439","1400–1468":"1400–1468","1430–1468":"1430–1468","1433–1498":"1433–1498","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1437–1495":"1437–1495","1437":"1437","1402":"1402","1435":"1435","1468":"1468","1433":"1433","1400":"1400","1498":"1498","1430":"1430","149